                type="document" xml:id="d668">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On May 5, 1954, the Paraguayan Army deposed President <persName corresp="#p_CF1"
                        >Federico Cháves</persName>, and the National Assembly thereupon named
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTR1">Tomás Romero Pereira</persName>, President of
                    the Governing Board of the Colorado Party, as Provisional President of Paraguay.
                    He served in that capacity until August 15, 1954, when General <persName
                        corresp="#p_SA1">Stroessner</persName>, having been duly elected on July 11
                    to fill the unexpired term of President <persName corresp="#p_CF1"
                        >Cháves</persName>, assumed the office of President. Documents pertaining to
                    these events are in file 734.00 and 734.00(W) for 1954.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
